        <p data-uuid="4e1746f8c1fe4e05b6867d731b216e12">Another federal project, the Tennessee Valley Authority (TVA), hired people to build dams and generators. This brought electricity and jobs to communities in the Tennessee River valley. The New Deal also included programs to help farmers. The Farm Credit Administration (FCA) helped farmers refinance their mortgages so they could keep their farms. The Agricultural Adjustment Act (AAA) helped stabilize agricultural prices.<br />
        </p>
